## 5. Stat tiles (live)

| Tile | Meaning | Colour |
|---|---|---|
| Median outcome | Middle of the distribution | teal if ≥0, coral if <0 |
| 1-in-20 downside | 5th-percentile floor | coral |
| Typical max drawdown | Median worst dip along the path | coral |
| Chance of losing >25% | Share of paths finishing >25% down | coral |
| Effective BTC beta | Market sensitivity after the hedge | amber |
| **BTC funding rate** | Annualized BTC perp funding (live Bybit, `· live`; fallback ~11%) | neutral |
| **Cost of insurance** | Hedge carry over the horizon — `−$X`, with `% · instrument · horizon`; `$0` when no hedge | amber |

All tiles update on every input change.

---

## 6. "Why these numbers" panel

A live, plain-language explanation that **rewrites itself** as inputs change. It must:
- Name the **biggest risk driver** (the asset contributing most modelled volatility) and its share.
- Explain that most of the risk is shared BTC market risk (why the tail is deep).
- When **no hedge**: describe what adding one (BTC, or MSTR if the broker won't allow shorting crypto) would do.
- When **hedged**: quantify the floor lift (from → to), note the median barely moves, state the **carry cost** and **upside given up**, and the new effective beta.
- When **MSTR**: add that basis risk remains and the floor lifts a little less than a direct BTC short.
- It **explains**, never recommends.

---

## 7. Model behaviour (UX-relevant)

- **Zero-drift volatility model**, client-side. Models dispersion, not predicted return — surfaced in copy.
- Assets share a **common BTC market factor + idiosyncratic noise**, so a BTC hedge genuinely reduces variance.
- **Fixed random seed:** the cone responds to *user input*, not to simulation noise. Changing one control must move only what that change implies.
- ~3,000 Monte-Carlo paths, recomputed on every input.
- Recompute is throttled to animation frames so dragging stays smooth.

---

## 8. Visual system

- **Dark mode, minimal, precise.** Deep cool-ink background (near-black, slightly blue), lifted panel surfaces, hairline borders, generous whitespace.
- **One accent: amber `#f5a524`**, used sparingly (a nod to the trading-terminal lineage).
- **Red `#ff6f6f` (downside) and teal `#4fd1c5` (upside)** are reserved strictly for meaning — never decoration.
- **Type:** headings in a clean confident sans; all numbers in monospace with tabular figures.
- No emoji. No gradient-soup. The cone is the one bold element.
- **Tweaks panel** (optional, host-toggled): cone style, panel surface, background tone, fonts, accent.

---

## 9. States & resilience

- **Loading:** snapshot data renders immediately; live Bybit prices and funding swap in when they arrive.
- **Live-data failure:** silent, labelled fallback to snapshot — no error UI, demo unaffected.
- **No-hedge state:** worst-case, cost ($0), and explanation all read sensibly at hedge = 0.
- **Reduced motion (landing):** entrance animations are skipped; content is shown, never left hidden.
- **Responsive:** controls stack below the chart on narrow screens; tiles reflow; hit targets ≥44px.

---

## 10. Compliance / guardrails (must remain true in UI)

- "Educational · not investment advice" is always visible.
- Footer disclaimer present on every surface: simulated from modelled volatility, **not forecasts**; **does not recommend** any position, allocation, or hedge; educational use only.
- No language anywhere that recommends an action or predicts a price.
